{"cursor":"22682","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox VG\n| title = Minerva image = caption = Minerva: Metastasis developer = Adam Foster\n| license = Freeware engine = Source engine released = Metastasis 1: Sept. 2,\n| 2005  Metastasis 2: March 12, 2006\n|   Metastasis 3 & 4: Oct. 1, 2007 genre = First-person shooter and puzzle modes\n| = Single-player platforms = Microsoft Windows media = Download requirements =\n| 1.2 GHz processor, 256 MB RAM, DirectX 7 level graphics card, input =\n| Keyboard, Mouse\n}} 'Minerva', (stylized as 'MINERVA') is an episodic series of single-player\nmods for Valve Corporation's [[Half-Life 2]] . The mod was created\nby Adam Foster. Installments are released as each is finalized: the three\nreleases for the Metastasis chapter have already been made, with the third\ninstallment released on October 1, 2007.\n\nThe plot and settings of Minerva are linked to Someplace Else, Foster's\noriginal map for [[Half-Life (video game)|Half-Life]], and to Half-Life\n2 itself.\n\nFoster describes Minerva as an \"anti-modification\": \"The aim isn't to replace as\nmuch game content as possible; instead, it's to tell my own apocryphal story set\nin the Half-Life 2 universe, and to actually release something for the public to\nplay.\" [http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=144068%20min\nInterview: Half-Life 2 Minerva mod], PC Zone Staff, Computer and Video Games,\nAugust 8, 2006, accessed October 3, 2007\n\nThe mod was released on Steam on April 30, 2013. http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2013-04-30-acclaimed-half-life-2-\nmod-minerva-polished-up-and-released-on-steam http://kotaku.com/free-\nhalf-life-2-mod-minerva-is-enhanced-and-up-on-st-486096778\n","linknr":301,"url":"Minerva_(video_game)","recorded":1375085373,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Minerva_(video_game)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Minerva_(video_game)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikiped